data.name: Label7.Text
data.value: The game ends when the game board is filled or when neither player can make a legal move. This includes all of the tiles being one player's color. From there the winner is decided based on which player has the most tiles on the board.

data.name: Label3.Text
data.value: To begin the game player one will make the first move by placing a tile to create a row with their color tiles on both ends of it. This row can be horizontal, vertical, or diagonal and must include at least one of the opponent's tiles in the middle of the row.
